# Quality Rules

Before finishing a task:
- run formatting
- run type checks if available
- run tests if available
- ensure Docker Compose still starts
- update README when setup changes

Code quality:
- small functions
- explicit types
- no hidden magic
- no unused abstractions
- no premature generic frameworks
- no TODOs without issue-style explanation

Documentation:
- document API examples
- document rule format
- document environment variables
- document known V1 limitations

Security:
- never commit real API keys
- use .env.example
- validate all external input
- do not log secrets
